    "content": "<p>In the frame shown in the figure (not to scale), all four members (AB, BC, CD, and AD) have the same length and same constant flexural rigidity. All the joints A, B, C, and D are rigid joints. The midpoints of AB, BC, CD, and AD, are denoted by E, F, G, and H, respectively. The frame is in unstable equilibrium under the shown forces of magnitude 𝑃 acting at E and G. Which of the following statements is/are TRUE?</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzaabwy9/92194586-5075-4805-95a0-90814df0be43/6d5c3010-4f79-11ef-8756-95a83bc0ffaa/file-jaoe38c1lzaabwya.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzaabwy9/92194586-5075-4805-95a0-90814df0be43/6d5c3010-4f79-11ef-8756-95a83bc0ffaa/file-jaoe38c1lzaabwya.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 3 English\">",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<span style=\"\">Shear forces at H and F are zero</span>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<span style=\"\">Horizontal displacements at H and F are zero</span>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<span style=\"\">Vertical displacements at H and F are zero</span>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<span style=\"\">Slopes at E, F, G, and H are zero</span>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A",
      "B",
      "D"
    ],
    "explanation": "<ul>\n<li><strong>Shear Forces at H and F</strong>: Since members AD and BC are subjected to pure bending, the shear force at points H and F is zero. This can be expressed mathematically as :</li>\n</ul>\n<p>$   V = \\frac{dM}{dx} = 0 \\quad \\text{(Zero)}   $</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Horizontal Displacements at H and F</strong>: The horizontal displacement at points H and F is zero due to symmetry and rigidity of the joints.</li><br>\n<li><strong>Vertical Displacements at H and F</strong>: The vertical displacement at points H and F is not zero, which indicates there is some vertical movement.</li><br>\n<li><strong>Slopes at E, F, G, and H</strong>: The slopes at points E, F, G, and H are zero because, in a symmetric deflection profile, the slope must be zero at the axis of symmetry.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Thus, the correct statements are :</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Shear forces at H and F are zero.</li><br>\n<li>Horizontal displacements at H and F are zero.</li><br>\n<li>Slopes at E, F, G, and H are zero.</li>\n</ul>",
    "answer": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2023-set-2",
    "difficulty": null
  },
