    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Consider the beam $A C D E B$ given in the figure. Which of the following statements is/ are correct:</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbiy7fcr/fd2a09f7-14d8-46ad-b520-94af25a2aaa2/a95f34b0-41cf-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbiy7fcs.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbiy7fcr/fd2a09f7-14d8-46ad-b520-94af25a2aaa2/a95f34b0-41cf-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbiy7fcs.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 1 English\">",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Bending moment is zero between the points A and C\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "There is a sudden jump in shear force at the point D\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "There is a sudden jump in bending moment at the point E\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Bending moment is zero somewhere between the points D and E"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A",
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { Let } V_A \\text { and } V_D \\text { be the vertical reactions at } A \\text { and } D \\text { respectively. } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbiy9az1/975e5325-623e-4a9d-bf12-9889333670dc/dd9b17d0-41cf-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbiy9az2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbiy9az1/975e5325-623e-4a9d-bf12-9889333670dc/dd9b17d0-41cf-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbiy9az2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 1 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp;\\text { From right side, }\\\\ &amp;\\begin{aligned} \\Sigma M_B &amp; =0 \\\\ -V_D(4)+4(2)+2(6) &amp; =0 \\end{aligned} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} \\Rightarrow &amp; &amp; V_D &amp; =5 \\mathrm{kN} \\\\ \\text { Also, } &amp; &amp; V_A+V_D &amp; =5 \\\\ &amp; &amp; V_A &amp; =0, M_A=0 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\text { SFD: } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbiyd2u5/472e7383-3af8-4e89-a6a6-d26691093688/468ec4d0-41d0-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbiyd2u6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbiyd2u5/472e7383-3af8-4e89-a6a6-d26691093688/468ec4d0-41d0-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbiyd2u6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 1 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\text { BMD: } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbiydph4/1f5e8dbc-d823-49f3-a02a-e7745841ad7d/580b8b80-41d0-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbiydph5.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbiydph4/1f5e8dbc-d823-49f3-a02a-e7745841ad7d/580b8b80-41d0-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbiydph5.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 1 English Explanation 3\"></p>\n<p>BM is zero in span AB and in between C and D . Correct answer will be (a) and (d).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2025-set-1",
