  {
    "direction": null,
    "comprehension": null,
    "content": "<p>A beam is subjected to a system of coplanar forces as shown in the figure. The magnitude of vertical reaction at Support P is ______ N (round off to one decimal place).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz8u0k1s/a49c33bc-0ce8-485a-89af-7468174d72a6/d6c71f10-4eac-11ef-af17-7d96bd734483/file-jaoe38c1lz8u0k1t.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz8u0k1s/a49c33bc-0ce8-485a-89af-7468174d72a6/d6c71f10-4eac-11ef-af17-7d96bd734483/file-jaoe38c1lz8u0k1t.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 2 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz8u2d1o/ae79c3dd-b15c-42e7-bff6-939fafd2ea67/08fc5cc0-4ead-11ef-af17-7d96bd734483/file-jaoe38c1lz8u2d1p.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz8u2d1o/ae79c3dd-b15c-42e7-bff6-939fafd2ea67/08fc5cc0-4ead-11ef-af17-7d96bd734483/file-jaoe38c1lz8u2d1p.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 2 English Explanation\">\n\n<p>Taking moment about hinge support $Q$,</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\quad \\Sigma M_Q=0 \\\\\\\\ &amp; P \\times(2+1.5+1+1.5)+(100 \\times 0.5)+(200 \\times 2.5) \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\quad-500 \\sin 60 \\times 4=0 \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\therefore P=197 \\mathrm{~N} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct answer is 197 .</p>",
    "answer": "196.6TO197.5",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2023-set-2",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "comprehension": null,
    "content": "<p>Consider the beam shown in the figure (not to scale), on a hinge support at end A and a roller support at end B. The beam has a constant flexural rigidity, and is subjected to the external moments of magnitude M at one-third spans, as shown in the figure. Which of the following statements is/are TRUE?</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzek1k1h/a2623ff0-2f5b-4ac5-976c-8f3bdac70f10/8b2f4e50-51d2-11ef-8aa8-1f39f1b8fc21/file-jaoe38c1lzek1k1i.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzek1k1h/a2623ff0-2f5b-4ac5-976c-8f3bdac70f10/8b2f4e50-51d2-11ef-8aa8-1f39f1b8fc21/file-jaoe38c1lzek1k1i.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 4 English\">",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<span style=\"\">Support reactions are zero</span>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<span style=\"\">Shear force is zero everywhere</span>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<span style=\"\">Bending moment is zero everywhere</span>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<span style=\"\">Deflection is zero everywhere</span>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A",
      "B"
    ],
    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzek4tu7/fcdb8290-6af6-4ff7-a6fb-7c6e0653f9af/e62e49f0-51d2-11ef-8aa8-1f39f1b8fc21/file-jaoe38c1lzek4tu8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzek4tu7/fcdb8290-6af6-4ff7-a6fb-7c6e0653f9af/e62e49f0-51d2-11ef-8aa8-1f39f1b8fc21/file-jaoe38c1lzek4tu8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 4 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<p>Equilibrium equations :</p>\n\n<p>$\\sum M_A=0$</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{array}{ll}   \\Rightarrow  -M+M-R_B \\times(3 L)=0 \\\\\\\\ \\Rightarrow  R_B=0 \\\\\\\\ \\sum F_V=0,  R_A+R_B=0 \\end{array} $$</p>\n\n<p>$\\Rightarrow R_A=0$</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzekbe5x/290e7973-88df-4b51-a399-bd80efb8782d/9cbc9a50-51d3-11ef-8aa8-1f39f1b8fc21/file-jaoe38c1lzekbe5y.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzekbe5x/290e7973-88df-4b51-a399-bd80efb8782d/9cbc9a50-51d3-11ef-8aa8-1f39f1b8fc21/file-jaoe38c1lzekbe5y.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 4 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>There are no shear forces throughout the span.</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzekbc0q/a3d249a5-0a93-49dc-9c69-c85472fc3c1b/9b148fa0-51d3-11ef-8aa8-1f39f1b8fc21/file-jaoe38c1lzekbc0r.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzekbc0q/a3d249a5-0a93-49dc-9c69-c85472fc3c1b/9b148fa0-51d3-11ef-8aa8-1f39f1b8fc21/file-jaoe38c1lzekbc0r.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 4 English Explanation 3\">\n\n<p>Here, bending moment and deflection is not zero everywhere.</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct options are (A), (B).</p>",
    "answer": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2023-set-1",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "content": "Consider the three prismatic beams with the clamped supports $$P,Q$$ and $$R$$ as shown in the figures.\n<img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/XC7QQTYrwMw6c3PS6/EFKMp444x6KmEAqzlJtUF0tGFSTfO/PF4K75eiOs8QUWWyeGYfUH/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"GATE CE 2017 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Shear Force and Bending Moment Question 6 English\">\n<p>Given that the modulus of elasticity, $$E$$ is $$2.5 \\times {10^4}\\,\\,MPa;$$ and the moment of inertia, $${\\rm I}$$ is $$8 \\times {10^3}\\,\\,m{m^4},$$ the correct comparison of the magnitudes of the shear force $$S$$ and the bending moment $$M$$ developed at the supports is </p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$${S_p} &lt; {S_Q} &lt; {S_R};{M_P} = {M_Q} = {M_R}$$ "
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$${S_p} = {S_Q} &gt; {S_R};{M_P} = {M_Q} &gt; {M_R}$$ "
      },
